title: For Sale:  Syrac Ordnance .750, Pistol Length, Clamp-On, AR 15, Adjustable Piston System
postcontent: This is the Syrac Ordnance New Low Pro Fully Adjustable Retro Fit Gas Piston System for the AR15 style platform.  This Piston System replaces the standard AR15 impingement gas system. It makes the rifle run much cleaner without blowing burnt carbon into the upper receiver Group. The piston gas block is low profile and fits under most handguards in the market. It will fit with any barrel nut (if a gas tube fits, the piston rod will fit).  The Syrac Ordnance piston system has a gas adjustment screw that is accessed from the font of the gas block with a Allen Key (included). The gas screw is locked into position by a click adjustment. The gas adjustment screw allows you to adjust the amount of gas that enters the system to reduce recoil. You are able to fine turn your rifle based on the type of ammo you use and/or if you are using a silencer. You have the option of completely turning the gas off which causes the rifle to not cycle.  All parts, including the gas screw, are removable for cleaning purposes.   Specifications:  Firearm Type: AR15 Gas Length: Pistol Barrel Diameter: 0.750" Weight: 12.6 oz. Bolt Carrier: Carrier body and key are one solid piece. Skis on the back of carrier. Gas Block Attachment Type: Clamp-on Gas Adjustment: Front of gas block  Included:  Piston System with one-piece carrier (key is integral to carrier) (1) 3/32" X 6" Hex Key tool to adjust gas screw) (1) 9/64" X 6" Hex key tool to install/remove gas block plug

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 4006TSW 40 cal. TACTICAL  + Extras
postcontent: The Smith & Wesson 4006 was introduced in January 1990 as the 1st US pistol made for the new .40 cal. round known as the 40 S&W. It has a 4" barrel and 11 round double stack magazine. The action is called Traditional Double Action (TDA) which describes a longer 1st shot trigger pull which cocks the hammer, and single action short crisp trigger pull on subsequent shots. An ambidextrous safety / decocker is featured for convenience and ultimate safety. There is also a loaded chamber indicator.Construction is all stainless steel and they're frankly built like tanks. They became a huge hit with law enforcement throughout the 90's due to absolute dependability and the awesome stopping power of the round. In 1997, this Model 4006TSW was intoduced. It features a rail under the frame for light or laser sight attachment, thicker full length frame rails for enhanced accuracy, and delayed unlocking to reduce felt recoil. That and it's 37.8 oz. weight is why they're known as the softest shooting therefore most controllable pistols ever made to fire the normally snappy 40 S&W round.This later production pistol I have for sale was made 6/22/2001. I tuned it up with new factory Novak Lo-Mount 3 dot sights, a new recoil spring, and added Hogue rubber grips which make this tack driver a dream to shoot.It's been well cared for as you can see. The internals are excellent since you simply can't wear out a 3rd Gen Smith. I know since my collection has grown to 18 of them. I hate to sell it but I just don't need 2 of this model. Along with a factory magazine with the latest version blue follower, EXTRAS are included like an S&W case, a new box of 50 rounds with the popular Hornady Self Defense XTP hollow point 180 grain bullet, the original factory straight grips, and an optional factory curved grip some may prefer. No trades please. The cash price is firm.
